oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Gay Street, 1869
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: unknown
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Gay Street, north from Main Street, Knoxville, TN. 1869. Shows people standing in street, horses and buggies in background. Signs include: East Tenn. Land Agency,____nson & Seymour; Cruze & Admey (Adney?) & Co.; W.W. Woodruff; T.M. Schleier's Picture Gallery; F. Heart; Star Billiards; McMillan & Co.; Gilbert & Co. Book Store; Chamberlain Bros. Drug; M.P. Chapin Book Store; Cowan & Dickinson. Lamar House at left. Possibly taken by T.M. Schleier.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Streets; Business enterprises;
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Photo File, Subject File, McClung Historical Collection
